    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-11T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-11T22:00:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/759: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-12T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 12, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 12—12:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Following from American Consul General at Harbin, <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 11, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>January 9th. General Lin<note n="68" xml:id="d47fn68">Presumably
                                    Geh. Li Tu, the Kirin commander.</note> crossed border to Iman
                                where interned by Soviet military. Japanese military have demanded
                                his return. They now possess Muling coal mines also Mishan.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>January 8th Suifenho garrison took oath of allegiance to
                                Manchukuo.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Japanese operations are continuing against General Wang Teh-lin
                                reported to be at Tungning.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>Whereabouts General Ting Chao unknown to this office.</item>
                            <label>5.</label>
                            <item>I leave this afternoon for Manchuli.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
